   “It will slow down investment in the oil and gas sector.  Foreign investments were coming in with full force because of the critical reforms that the bill came to address in the oil and gas. What this means is that any investment that suppose to come to the sector by the end of this month, may be placed on hold and consequently, the nation will lose out such opportunity.  This kind of a thing will not bother those who are not working for the national interest. The investment that should have come this week may be delayed for one or two weeks, but they will surely come. 
  
The Chairman, Petroleum Technology Association of Nigeria (PETAN), Bank-Anthony Okoroafor, said that the PIGB emphasized the need for the President to ascent to the bill as soon as possible.He also stressed the need for the passage of Petroleum Industry Administration Bill, Petroleum Industry Fiscal Bill and the Petroleum Host Community Bill.
  
“We need the governance bill to set up the framework to create efficient and effective governing institutions with clear and separate roles, establish a framework for the creation of commercially-oriented and profit driven entities, promote transparency and accountability as well as foster a conducive business environment,” he said To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .